note over browser:
The user types some data in the form and presses submit
end note
browser->server: HTTP POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_noteserver
note over browser:
The browser sends a new data to the server
end note
server->browser: redirect to https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/notes
note over server:
The server responds by redirecting to exampleapp/notes
end note

browser->server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/notes
server->browser: HTML-code
browser->server: HTTP GET main.css
server->browser: main.css
browser->server: HTTP GET main.js
server->browser: main.js

note over browser:
The browser starts excuting js code that requests JSON data from the server
end note

browser->server: HTTP GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
server->browser: data.json

note over browser:
When the data is passed, it triggers an event in Javascript. This causes javascript
to execute a code within the event. This code loops through the data
and adds list of notes to the HTML
end note
